openapi: 3.0.0 info: title: Bulk API version: 2.0.0 description: | The API for performing bulk uploads

File Preparation

This API requires a file to be submitted with the appropriate schema. The details of that file's schema can be found at File schema tags: - name: UploadAllParticipants servers: - url: '/bulk/{stateAbbr}/v2' variables: stateAbbr: default: none description: Lowercase two-letter postal code abbreviation paths: '/upload_all_participants/{filename}': put: operationId: upload_all_participants summary: Upload a CSV file of bulk participant data tags: - Bulk Upload parameters: - name: filename in: path description: Name of file being uploaded required: true schema: type: string - in: header name: Content-Length schema: type: integer required: true description: Size in bytes of your file to be uploaded. A curl request will add this header by default when including a data or file parameter. example: 6413 requestBody: content: text/plain: schema: type: string format: binary responses: '201': description: File uploaded content: application/json: schema: title: Upload response type: object properties: data: type: object nullable: true description: The response payload. Will contain a data property with upload details. required: - upload_id properties: upload_id: type: string description: A unique upload_id for the successful upload. examples: Default: description: An upload of a single CSV file of all the participants value: data: upload_id: '0x8DA2EA86C4C2089' '401': description: Access denied '411': description: Content-Length not provided '/upload/{filename}': put: operationId: upload (deprecated) summary: Deprecated. This endpoint has been renamed to `upload_all_participants` and will be removed in a future version. Upload a CSV file of bulk participant data. tags: - Bulk Upload parameters: - name: filename in: path description: Name of file being uploaded required: true schema: type: string - in: header name: Content-Length schema: type: integer required: true description: Size in bytes of your file to be uploaded. A curl request will add this header by default when including a data or file parameter. example: 6413 requestBody: content: text/plain: schema: type: string format: binary responses: '201': description: File uploaded content: application/json: schema: title: Upload response type: object properties: data: type: object nullable: true description: The response payload. Will contain a data property with upload details. required: - upload_id properties: upload_id: type: string description: A unique upload_id for the successful upload. examples: Default: description: An upload of a single CSV file of all the participants value: data: upload_id: '0x8DA2EA86C4C2089' '401': description: Access denied '411': description: Content-Length not provided security: - ApiKeyAuth: [] components: securitySchemes: ApiKeyAuth: type: apiKey in: header name: Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key
